MANUAL SWC-REGISTRY CHECKLIST — applied to all contracts
(Run in addition to slither, per 04-CONTEXT HARD-03 clause.)
Contracts: src/Cascade.sol, src/aa/CascadeAccount.sol,
           src/aa/AccountFactory.sol, src/aa/{IEntryPoint,IAccount,PackedUserOperation}.sol
================================================================

[SWC-101] Integer Over/Underflow
  CONCLUSION: NOT VULNERABLE. Pragma ^0.8.24 → checked arithmetic by default.
  - Cascade.register: `id = ++skillCount` (checked), `shareSum += depShares[i]`
    bounded by `shareSum > BPS revert`. depth = maxDepDepth+1 bounded by MAX_DEPTH=8.
  - Cascade._distribute: `routed = amount*depShares[i]/BPS` — multiplication is checked;
    depShares[i] <= 10000 by register-time invariant; amount <= original msg.value.
    `creatorCut = amount - routedSum` cannot underflow: routedSum is a sum of
    floor(amount*share/BPS) terms whose shares sum to <= BPS, so routedSum <= amount.
  - CascadeAccount: no unchecked blocks; loop index `++i` checked.

[SWC-104] Unchecked Call Return Value
  CONCLUSION: HANDLED, distinction is intentional & documented.
  - Cascade.claim L146-147: return value CHECKED — `if (!ok) revert TransferFailed()`.
  - CascadeAccount._payPrefund L97-98: return value INTENTIONALLY IGNORED `(ok);`.
    Rationale: ERC-4337 v0.7 BaseAccount semantics — the EntryPoint itself enforces the
    prefund; the account must not revert here or it breaks validation. Documented in NatSpec.
  - CascadeAccount._call L104-109: success CHECKED — bubbles inner revert via assembly.

[SWC-105/106] Unprotected Withdrawal / SELFDESTRUCT
  CONCLUSION: NOT VULNERABLE.
  - No selfdestruct anywhere.
  - Cascade.claim only ever pays msg.sender its own accrued balance (then zeroes it).
  - CascadeAccount.execute/executeBatch gated by onlyEntryPointOrOwner.
  - CascadeAccount.validateUserOp gated by `msg.sender == entryPoint` (NotFromEntryPoint).

[SWC-107] Reentrancy
  CONCLUSION: NOT VULNERABLE.
  - Cascade.claim follows strict CEI: balance zeroed (effect) BEFORE the external
    call (interaction). A re-entrant claim sees balance 0 → no double-pay.
  - Cascade._distribute performs NO external calls — pure internal balance credits,
    so the recursive fan-out is reentrancy-safe and no payee can block the tree.
  - slither flags only "reentrancy-events" (event emitted after call in claim) — this is
    informational; no state mutation follows the call, so it is not exploitable. ACCEPTED.

[SWC-113 / SWC-128] DoS (failed call / unbounded operation / gas-limit)
  CONCLUSION: NOT VULNERABLE.
  - Pull-payment model: a single failing payee cannot block others (each claims own).
  - _distribute recursion bounded by MAX_DEPTH=8, enforced at register time
    (DepthExceeded). Per-skill dep arrays are caller-supplied but each invoke pays a
    fixed price and traverses a tree whose depth is capped; breadth is paid for by the caller.
  - executeBatch loops over caller-supplied arrays (length checked equal); caller bears gas.

[SWC-115] Authorization through tx.origin
  CONCLUSION: NOT VULNERABLE. `tx.origin` appears nowhere. All auth uses msg.sender.

[SWC-117] Signature Malleability
  CONCLUSION: NOT VULNERABLE. CascadeAccount._recover enforces EIP-2 low-s:
  `if (uint256(s) > SECP256K1_HALF_N) return address(0)` and `v in {27,28}`, plus
  65-byte length check and address(0) rejection. Returns address(0) on any anomaly so
  validateUserOp reports SIG_VALIDATION_FAILED (never reverts). Replay is bound by the
  EntryPoint userOpHash (chainId + EntryPoint + nonce), not this contract's concern.

[SWC-103] Floating Pragma
  CONCLUSION: ACCEPTED (informational). Pragma is `^0.8.24`. Caret floats forward within
  0.8.x. For a hackathon/local build this is intentional (forge pins solc 0.8.24 via
  foundry.toml). Documented in SECURITY.md as an accepted LOW; pin to `=0.8.24` only at
  mainnet-deploy time if reproducible-bytecode verification requires it.

[Other classes checked — no finding]
  - SWC-116 (block.timestamp dependence): not used for logic.
  - SWC-120 (weak randomness): no randomness used.
  - SWC-132 (unexpected ether balance): Cascade never relies on address(this).balance for
    accounting — it tracks `balances[]` explicitly; force-fed ether (selfdestruct) cannot
    corrupt the per-creator ledger.
  - Uninitialized-local (slither): shareSum/maxDepDepth/routedSum default to 0 in Solidity;
    relying on default-zero init is safe and idiomatic. ACCEPTED informational.
  - missing-zero-check on owner (slither): constructor arg; a zero owner simply yields an
    unusable account (no valid signer). Factory callers control the arg. ACCEPTED LOW.
  - too-many-digits (slither): the 0xff CREATE2 prefix literal. Standard, ACCEPTED informational.
